{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2632abbd-2636-4ffe-a9b3-559d5fffc8f2","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then rebuild & test:**\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\ndotnet test   # if you have tests\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages targeting `net10.0` specifically — update those to versions that support `net11.0`. You can run `dotnet list package --outdated` to find them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3195ed2a-17ee-4052-9a1b-ac8ec870126e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question about upgrading .NET versions. I can answer this directly without needing to search any codebase.","outputTokens":294,"requestId":"2838:81419:1552E5B:17FC52A:6A0285AB"},"id":"acc68790-4e64-4d94-8459-8367437e5bf4","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:43:13.553Z","parentId":"bd3ca29a-3e09-499d-826f-392486ede689"}
